sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Notebook
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API
    participant Kueue as Kueue Controller
    participant TrainOp as Training Operator
    participant Workers as Worker Pods
    participant S3 as S3 / PVC Storage
    participant FMS as FMS HF Tuning
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry
    participant KServe as KServe

    Note over User,KServe: Workflow 2: Distributed Training Job Submission

    User->>Notebook: Write training code<br/>in Jupyter workbench
    Notebook->>S3: Download training data<br/>(HTTPS/443, AWS IAM)

    User->>K8sAPI: Submit PyTorchJob CR<br/>(kubectl or KFP SDK)

    Kueue->>K8sAPI: Watch: new workload intercepted
    Kueue->>Kueue: Evaluate quota against<br/>ClusterQueue / LocalQueue
    Note over Kueue: Wait for resources if queue full
    Kueue->>K8sAPI: Admit workload<br/>(set admission status)

    TrainOp->>K8sAPI: Watch: admitted PyTorchJob
    TrainOp->>K8sAPI: Create worker Pods<br/>+ headless Service for DNS
    TrainOp->>K8sAPI: Set framework-specific env vars<br/>(MASTER_ADDR, WORLD_SIZE, etc.)

    Workers->>Workers: Distributed training<br/>(PyTorch DDP / DeepSpeed)
    Workers->>S3: Periodic checkpoint saves
    Workers->>Workers: NCCL / Gloo collective ops<br/>(pod-to-pod)

    FMS->>Workers: SFT / LoRA fine-tuning<br/>(specialized training image)
    FMS->>S3: Save final model<br/>to output volume

    User->>ModelReg: Register trained model<br/>(gRPC/9090, mTLS)
    ModelReg->>S3: Store artifact reference

    User->>K8sAPI: Create InferenceService CR<br/>from registered model
    KServe->>ModelReg: Fetch model location<br/>(model-registry:// URI)
    KServe->>S3: Download model artifacts
    Note over KServe: Deploy model for serving
